Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A system for use with a watercraft, comprising: a watercraft device for coupling to, or forming part of, the watercraft, the watercraft device comprising a first watercraft lock component; a docking station comprising at least one second watercraft lock component configured to couple with at least the first watercraft lock component; and at least one microcontroller and at least one wireless communication component forming part of at least one of the watercraft device and docking station; wherein: at least one of the watercraft lock components configured to be placed in at least one of a locked state, where the watercraft device is secured to the docking station, and an unlocked state, where the watercraft device is removable from the docking station, by the at least one microcontroller; and the at least one microcontroller configured to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state in response to a signal received by the at least one wireless communication component. 2. The system of claim 1, further comprising at least one of: a server having at least one processor, at least one communication component, at least one data storage component containing program code for controlling server components to 

 communicate with at least one of the watercraft device, at least one mobile device, and the docking station, the server configured to selectively generate and transmit a server signal; and a mobile device having a processor, at least one wireless communication component, at least one data storage component containing program code for controlling mobile-device components to communicate with at least one of the watercraft device, the docking station, and the server, the mobile device configured to selectively generate and transmit a mobile-device signal; wherein at least one of the server signal and the mobile-device signal causes the at least one microcontroller to place the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state. 3. The system of claim 2, wherein: the first watercraft lock component comprises an electronic locking mechanism; and the watercraft device further comprises a processor, a microcontroller, a wireless communication component, a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the watercraft device to instruct the microcontroller of the watercraft device to place the first watercraft lock component in the unlocked state in response to the signal received by the wireless communication component of the watercraft device. 4. The system of claim 3, wherein the signal received by the watercraft device comprises the server signal. 5. The system of claim 4, wherein the server generates and transmits the server signal in response to the mobile-device signal received by the communication component of the server. 6. The system of claim 2, wherein: the second watercraft lock component comprises an electronic locking mechanism; and the docking station further comprises a processor, a microcontroller, a wireless communication component, a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the docking station to instruct the microcontroller of the docking station to place the second watercraft lock component in the unlocked state in response to the signal received by the wireless communication component of the docking station. 7. The system of claim 6, wherein the signal received by the docking station comprises the server signal. 8. The system of claim 7, wherein the server generates and transmits the server signal in response to the mobile-device signal received by the communication component of the server. 9. The system of claim 6, wherein: the watercraft device further comprises a processor, a wireless communication component, a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the watercraft device to communicate with the server and the docking station, the watercraft device configured to generate and transmit a watercraft-device signal in response to the server signal received by the wireless communication component of the watercraft device; wherein, the signal received by the docking station comprises the watercraft-device signal. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein the server generates and transmits the server signal in response to receiving the mobile-device signal. 11. The system of claim 1, further comprising: a watercraft equipment having a watercraft-equipment device comprising a first watercraft-equipment lock component; a second watercraft-equipment lock component forming part of at least one of the watercraft device and the docking station; wherein: at least one of the watercraft-equipment lock components configured to be placed in at least one of a locked state, where the watercraft equipment is secured to at least one of the watercraft device and the docking station, and an unlocked state, where the watercraft equipment is removable from at least one of the watercraft device and the docking station, by the at least one microcontroller; and the at least one microcontroller configured to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state in response to a signal received by the at least one wireless communication component. 12. The system of claim 11, further comprising: a server having at least one processor, at least one communication component, and at least one data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the 

 server to communicate with the watercraft device, the server configured to generate and transmit a server signal; wherein: the watercraft device further comprises a processor, a microcontroller, a wireless communication component, the second watercraft-equipment lock component comprising an electronic locking mechanism, and a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the watercraft device to communicate with the server and to instruct the microcontroller to place the second watercraft-equipment lock component in the unlocked state; and the signal received by the wireless communication component of the watercraft device is the server signal. 13. The system of claim 11, further comprising: a server having at least one processor, at least one communication component, and at least one data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the server to communicate with the watercraft device, the server configured to generate and transmit a server signal; wherein: the watercraft device further comprises a processor, a wireless communication component, and a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the watercraft device to communicate with the server and the docking station, the watercraft device configured to generate and transmit a watercraft-device signal; 

 the docking station further comprises a processor, a microcontroller, a wireless communication component, the second watercraft-equipment lock component comprising an electronic locking mechanism, and a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the docking station to communicate with the watercraft device and to instruct the microcontroller to place the second watercraft-equipment lock component in the unlocked state; and the signal received by the wireless communication component of the docking station is the watercraft-device signal. 14. The system of claim 11, further comprising: a server having at least one processor, at least one communication component, and at least one data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the server to communicate with the docking station, the server configured to generate and transmit a server signal; wherein: the docking station further comprises a processor, a microcontroller, a wireless communication component, the second watercraft-equipment lock component comprising an electronic locking mechanism, and a data storage component containing program code for controlling components of the docking station to communicate with the server and to instruct the microcontroller to place the second watercraft-equipment lock component in the unlocked state; and the signal received by the wireless communication component of the docking station is the server signal. 15. A watercraft device for selectively locking and unlocking a watercraft, the watercraft device comprising: a watercraft lock component; a unique identifier; a water resistant case housing: a processor; a power component electrically connected to the processor; a data storage component operatively coupled to the processor; a wireless communication component operatively coupled to the processor, the wireless communication component configured to communicate with at least one of a docking station, a server, and a mobile device; and a location tracking component operatively coupled to the processor. 16. A method for automated renting of watercraft, comprising: providing a watercraft system comprising: a watercraft device configured to attach to, or form part of, a watercraft, the watercraft device comprising a first watercraft lock component; at least one docking station comprising at least one second watercraft lock component configured to couple with at least one first watercraft lock component; at least one of the watercraft lock components configured to be placed in at least one of a locked state, where the watercraft is secured to the docking station, and an unlocked state, where the watercraft is removable from the docking station, by at least 

 one microcontroller, the at least one microcontroller configured to place the watercraft lock components in an unlocked state in response to a signal received by at least one wireless communication component, the at least one microcontroller and at least one wireless communication component forming part of at least one of the watercraft device and docking station; providing program code to a mobile device of a user, the mobile device comprising a processor, at least one wireless communication component, at least one data storage component, and at least one power component; receiving, at a server, a mobile-device signal, the mobile-device signal including application-request information generated by the program code and corresponding to a request to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in an unlocked state; sending from the server, to at least one of the watercraft device, the mobile device and the docking station, a server signal in response to the application-request information, the responsive server signal including watercraft-component information concerning at least one watercraft lock component; instructing a microcontroller to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state in response to receiving a signal containing watercraft-component information. 17. The method of claim 16, wherein the microcontroller instructed to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state forms part of the watercraft device and is operatively coupled to the first watercraft lock component of the watercraft device. 18. The method of claim 16, wherein the microcontroller instructed to place at least one of the watercraft lock components in the unlocked state forms part of the docking station and is operatively coupled to the second watercraft lock component of the docking station. 19. The method of claim 16, further comprising: providing a watercraft equipment having a first watercraft-equipment lock component, the first watercraft-equipment lock component configured to couple with at least one second watercraft lock component forming part of the docking station, the watercraft-equipment lock components configured to be placed in at least one of a locked state, where the watercraft- equipment is secured to the docking station, and an unlocked state, where the watercraft- equipment is removable from the docking station, by at least one microcontroller; instructing a microcontroller to place the second watercraft-equipment lock component in the unlocked state in response to a wireless communication component of the docking stating receiving at least one of a server signal, a mobile-device signal and a watercraft-device signal. 20. The method of claim 16, further comprising: providing a watercraft equipment having a first watercraft-equipment lock component, the first watercraft-equipment lock component configured to couple with at least one second watercraft lock component forming part of the watercraft device, the watercraft-equipment lock components configured to be placed in at least one of a locked state, where the watercraft- equipment is secured to the watercraft device, and an unlocked state, where the watercraft- equipment is removable from the watercraft device, by at least one microcontroller; 

 instructing a microcontroller to place the second watercraft-equipment lock component in the unlocked state in response to a wireless communication component of the watercraft device receiving at least one of a server signal, a docking-station signal and a mobile-device signal.
